Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Put a large #saucepan{} of water with a pinch of @salt{pinch} on to boil for the potato and broccoli. Chop the @baking potato{1} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel!). Separate the @broccoli florets{200} into florets (mini trees!). Trim the stalky tops from the @green beans{150}. Put the @British chicken breasts{2} between two sheets of #clingfilm{}, bash with a #rolling pin{} until 2cm thick.

Put the chicken breasts between two pieces of clingfilm and bash with a rolling pin or saucepan until 2cm thick. Lay the chicken on another foil-lined #baking tray{}. IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Pop the @creme fraiche{50%g} in a #small bowl{}. Add the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Stir together well. In another small bowl, mix the @panko breadcrumbs{30%g} with the @olive oil{2%tbsp} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Spoon equal amounts of the cheese mixture onto each chicken breast then spread with a #knife{} to coat the breast.

Next, spoon the breadcrumbs onto each breast, pressing lightly to make sure they stick. Bake on the top shelf of your oven until the crumbs are golden and the chicken is cooked through, ~{15-20%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle. Pop the broccoli tray on the middle shelf of the oven and roast until tender, ~{15%minutes}.

Trim and finely slice the @spring onion{1} then do any washing up that needs doing. When the potato is cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat. Add a pinch of @salt{pinch}, @pepper{pinch} and a @?butter{knob} and mash with a #potato masher{}. Stir through the spring onion then cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

Remove the chicken and broccoli from the oven when ready. Share the mash between your #plates{} and serve the chicken and broccoli alongside. Enjoy!

> This recipe is perfect for mid-week when you're longing for the weekend and need a bit of comfort food - crispy, golden and gooey chicken with creamy broccoli mash and simple stir-fried green beans.